The paper deals with fair division, a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of graphs as the resource being divided suggests a possible connection to graph theory (cs.SI). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and optimization, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
